1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,320
<i>Were you trying to kill Kanah?</i>

2
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:45,240
- Hey, Bung. Bung.
- Pakbung.

3
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,120
Please let me get to know my dad too.

4
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:51,760
How will you, an orphan with no roots,

5
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:54,800
stripped of your father's influence,
keep living in this society?

6
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:58,400
<i>Because I'm the only one</i>
<i>who can give you what you want.</i>

7
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:01,760
<i>Then I'd like to congratulate</i>
<i>the next CEO.</i>

8
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,440
And don't forget Dad's intention.

9
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,560
Someone cheated?

10
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:09,520
You have to find evidence and expose them.

11
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,760
Proof of how they cheated you.

12
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,000
Mr. Pittaya, the IT Department head,
already confessed to us

13
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,040
that he was the one who did it.

14
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,280
- What do you want?
- You should already know

15
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,000
what I want.

16
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,800
He's fooling you too.

17
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:28,240
Trai has never truly loved anyone.
He only loves himself.

18
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,480
Mr. Trai.

19
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:53,200
I couldn't sleep at all last night
because of what you said.

20
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:56,960
You didn't look like the type to overthink

21
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:57,920
other people's words.

22
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,200
- Pakbung, you don't have to--
- Wait.

23
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,160
I want to talk to Ms. Darin.

24
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:06,320
You said Mr. Trai doesn't know
how to love anyone?

25
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,520
That he only loves himself?

26
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,840
Yes.

27
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:13,240
And why does that bother you?

28
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:16,600
Or do you think you're the exception?

29
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:20,320
That he loves you so much?
Try having a real problem.

30
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:24,600
He'll leave you and save himself
without a second thought.

31
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,120
Then didn't you leave him too?

32
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,200
You said Mr. Trai only loves himself.

33
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,040
But what about you?

34
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:37,120
Did you love him
more than you loved yourself?

35
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,560
What do you want, Pakbung?

36
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:49,560
So what if Mr. Trai loves himself?
I do. You do.

37
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,400
Everyone loves themselves first.

38
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,360
That's perfectly normal.

39
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,960
Why does that have to be his fault?

40
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,280
He left you, you left him.

41
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,080
He hurt you, you hurt him.

42
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,400
It's the same. There's no difference.

43
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,840
Stop dumping all the blame on him alone.

44
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:11,000
Share the guilt too.

45
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,800
You're not me. You wouldn't understand.

46
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,920
I'm not here to understand.

47
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,400
I just wanted to say what I think.

48
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,160
Maybe you'll think about it too.

49
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,680
Pakbung. Pakbung.

50
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,240
I don't know what's wrong with me.

51
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,400
Normally, I don't meddle
in other people's business,

52
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,680
and this isn't even my business.

53
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,840
Ms. Darin was insulting you, not me.

54
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,040
So why did I explode?

55
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:52,680
Why couldn't I calm down? Why am I
angry on your behalf? I don't get it.

56
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,960
Because you care about me.

57
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,680
I do, but it's too much.

58
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:02,400
Way too much. Am I crazy?

59
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:08,080
I'm yelling at myself, okay? Not you.

60
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,880
Not anyone else.
I'm just frustrated with myself.

61
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:15,160
Calm down. I think I know why.

62
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,480
- Because--
- I'm on my period.

63
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,680
My hormones are out of control.

64
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:25,760
I'm not myself.
I can't control my emotions.

65
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,480
I need to get a grip.

66
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:31,560
I need to go to work. Work helps me focus.

67
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:33,200
I'm going.

68
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,760
Pakbung. Pakbung.

69
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,120
Here, meatballs!

70
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,640
Perfect timing.

71
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,520
Alright.

72
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,080
You go first.

73
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,960
She's still practicing
on her inner energy or what?

74
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:01,960
Yeah.

75
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,200
She looks serious.

76
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,040
What's so hard about it?

77
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:10,560
You get worked up for him
because you have feelings for him.

78
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,200
Why blame it on your period?

79
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:16,800
Meditating like this
isn't gonna help much.

80
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:22,200
- I don't have feelings for him.
- You do.

81
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:24,960
No.

82
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:32,720
You don't have to listen to others,
but at least listen to your own heart.

83
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,560
Make your life easier.

84
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,160
- I--
- If I had your chance,

85
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,560
to be with a guy who's serious
and always there for me,

86
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:45,760
I wouldn't play hard to get.
By now, I'd have two kids in kindergarten.

87
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,800
Whoa, that's too much.

88
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:56,360
Or are you scared Trai will leave you?
Then date him

89
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,520
and dump him first.

90
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,160
- Kanah!
- Kanah!

91
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:03,120
What? Time keeps moving.

92
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,880
Your uterus has an expiration date too.

93
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:12,280
Amazing advice, all of you.

94
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,320
Alright. Do whatever you want.

95
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:17,840
If fear makes you comfortable,
then stay there.

96
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,000
But if I had a man,

97
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,720
if Niuniu had a man, if Kanah--

98
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,080
I can't have a man. Put your hand down.

99
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:29,200
Fine. And if you're single,

100
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:31,200
you can't complain that you're lonely.

101
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,240
Yeah.

102
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,000
Eat.

103
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,240
It's still hot.

104
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,200
If Mr. Trai were hitting on me,
I'd say yes

105
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,039
- on day one.
- Well, that's you. Right?

106
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:46,120
So, do you have any friends for us?

107
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,280
- Don't even try. I'm not introducing…
- Why?

108
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,600
…my friends to you.

109
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,640
- Why?
- Why?

110
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,320
You guys are terrifying.

111
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,680
If I really pay you this time,

112
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,400
will you tell me what's on your mind?

113
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:27,120
I'm thinking about the advice
my friends gave me.

114
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,560
Then let me give you one piece of advice.

115
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,120
Think less

116
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,640
and listen more
to what you feel right here.

117
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,800
You and Ms. Darin dated before.

118
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,080
You already know why we broke up.

119
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,280
Hearts can change.

120
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,040
All it takes is a reason.
Nothing lasts forever.

121
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:51,360
Pakbung, I know
you don't believe in promises.

122
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:55,040
You don't believe true love exists.
But I want you to trust your feelings--

123
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,320
I've decided.

124
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:02,400
- Do you want to try dating me, Mr. Trai?
- Huh?

125
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,640
Did you say that wrong? No.

126
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,240
Did I hear that wrong?

127
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,680
What did you hear?

128
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,640
"Do you want to try dating me?"

129
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:19,160
Yeah. Okay. Let's try.

130
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,560
Huh?

131
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,880
You asked Mr. Trai to be your boyfriend?!

132
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,480
You're dating Trai now?

133
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,360
Yeah.

134
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,200
Why are you guys so shocked?

135
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:33,080
You were cheering me on earlier.
I thought you'd be happy.

136
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,040
Come here.

137
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:44,400
I mean, I'm happy.

138
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:47,240
But earlier, you were still
confused, weren't you?

139
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,920
I figured it out

140
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,920
thanks to your advice.

141
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,000
Which advice?

142
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:59,200
Oh, "Date him and dump him"?

143
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:04,040
Or is she scared of being single forever?

144
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:10,160
Opportunity. Time. Fear.

145
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,720
Brilliant, Pakbung.

146
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,440
I knew you'd find the meaning

147
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:20,000
in our nonsense.

148
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,720
Mr. Trai,

149
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,200
why are you so quiet? Aren't you happy?

150
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:27,360
I'm not dreaming, right?

151
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,040
- Shall I try?
- Hey, hey.

152
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,080
I'm not dreaming, right?

153
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,040
Dreaming?

154
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,200
It's not a dream.

155
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:44,840
Wait, hold on. I don't get it.

156
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:50,000
Opportunity, time, fear, what is that?

157
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:55,480
I've always been afraid of change,

158
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,600
especially with people's hearts.

159
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:01,840
Today, someone loves you.
Tomorrow, they don't.

160
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:05,120
But when I really thought about it,

161
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:08,000
even if he stops liking me tomorrow,
he's still here with me today.

162
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,240
So I have to hurry before time runs out.

163
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,400
Before time runs out?

164
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,760
Uterus time?

165
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,400
Life!

166
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,840
We all die.

167
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,280
Well,

168
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,960
nothing in this world is certain anyway.

169
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:35,000
So I should take the chance
and make it count.

170
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,720
‪Sure.

171
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,880
Yes…

172
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,560
Let's go sit over there.

173
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,640
Yeah.

174
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,160
I was minding my own business,
and she had to come pick a fight.

175
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,000
She accused me
of dumping the blame on Trai.

176
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,320
Who is she to defend Trai? Shameless.

177
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,920
Are you angry because you're jealous?

178
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:30,000
I'm angry because she had
the nerve to lecture me.

179
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:34,640
She acts like she knows everything,
like what I went through was nothing.

180
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,200
My life is completely ruined.

181
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,600
I've been through hell.
You call that nothing?

182
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:40,280
Then how do you want me to help?

183
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,760
I want her to hurt.

184
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:46,480
I want her to suffer.
It'd be even better if she just died.

185
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,440
Hey.

186
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,360
Hey, why are you out here?

187
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,560
Get back in, get back in.

188
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,760
Don't come out, got it?

189
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,440
Hey, hey, he parked.

190
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,360
He got out already. Go.

191
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,280
Did he come?

192
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:16,040
- Did he come?
- He's here.

193
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,240
Come out now. Go.

194
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,400
Go now.

195
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,760
- Go.
- Walk properly.

196
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,760
Act cool. Walk properly.

197
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,840
For our first date.

198
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,600
You got me a gift?

199
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,640
I'm giving you… my body.

200
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,400
Then I'll be your gift too.

201
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:05,960
Rut, I want you
to look into Be Rich's shares,

202
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:11,720
who's been buying and selling,
and if anything looks off lately.

203
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,160
What are you suspecting, Mr. Rachen?

204
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,840
I just want proof.

205
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,640
Get me the full list
of everyone holding Be Rich shares.

206
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,640
Yes, sir.

207
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,800
He's having someone
investigate the shares?

208
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:40,960
I let it slide that he kept
Trai's customers under his care,

209
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,920
and now he's seriously
thinking of teaming up with Trai?

210
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:52,760
If Rachen joins hands with his brother,

211
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,760
that means he wants to be my enemy.

212
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,400
What should a traitor get?

213
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,880
Make it clean and fast.

214
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,480
I want them to regret
ever thinking they could be my enemy.

215
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,120
Yes, ma'am.

216
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,680
Is she going after just Mr. Rachen
or Mr. Trai too?

217
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,040
OPEN ENROLLMENT FOR NEW STUDENTS
DUANGDAO KINDERGARTEN

218
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,200
FROM PRE-KINDERGARTEN TO KINDERGARTEN 3

219
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,440
Is Pakbung gonna get dragged
into this too?

220
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:22,280
- Where's Rut?
- Mr. Rut said he had something

221
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,600
to handle for you,
so he told me to drive instead.

222
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,000
- Thank you.
- Thank you for coming to our school.

223
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,120
We'll contact you back.

224
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,200
- Thank you.
- Yes.

225
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:06,840
I never thought

226
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,320
interviewing teachers
would be this exhausting.

227
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:14,360
It's like I used up my whole
monthly brain quota in one day.

228
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:16,920
It's harder than selling stuff

229
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,520
and calculating math.

230
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,720
Am I gonna survive this?

231
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,280
Come here.

232
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,120
How is it? Feel good?

233
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:52,640
Good

234
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,040
but not quite there.

235
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:56,240
Oh?

236
00:19:57,520 --> 00:20:00,120
Here, this is how you do it.

237
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,160
- Oh, whoa.
- See?

238
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,200
Your muscles are hard as rocks.

239
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:07,480
So tight. Have you never had
a massage or what?

240
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,920
What are you doing?

241
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:21,000
That hurts. Enough. I can't take it.

242
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:23,920
Is that a knee or a log?

243
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,320
- I'm gonna be sore.
- Hey.

244
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,760
Where are you going? Where's my tip?

245
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,040
Coming back to tip me?

246
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:52,880
Um… well, I wanted to cook for Kanah,

247
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:57,320
but I don't know what he likes,
or if he has any allergies now,

248
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:00,880
so I called Samlee
and asked where you were,

249
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:04,360
and I wanted to ask you
to go grocery shopping with me.

250
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,960
You want to cook for Kanah?

251
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,760
Kanah isn't coming home today.

252
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,760
He already told you that.

253
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:14,760
You forgot, didn't you?

254
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,000
Well, I lied.

255
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,640
Actually, I wanted to do it for you.

256
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,600
I want to take care of you too.

257
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:33,560
Since I'm here, give me a chance

258
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:35,840
to be a father to you, please.

259
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:43,000
Do you want to go?

260
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:49,040
- I don't know.
- Then go.

261
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:50,960
Huh?

262
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:54,040
Normally, you'd refuse. You're hesitating,
so a part of you wants to go.

263
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,800
So go.

264
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:00,640
If it doesn't work, next time,
you won't have to hesitate again.

265
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:11,600
An opportunity like this
doesn't come often.

266
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,200
If there's a chance, take it.

267
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,880
Make the most of it.

268
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:43,800
So, you and Mr. Trai are you dating now?

269
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:46,800
Why do you ask?

270
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:51,360
Well, I was just making small talk.

271
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:08,720
You know, back then, you used to ride on
the back of my bike to school every day.

272
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,040
And?

273
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:11,640
You'd ask me to stop by the market

274
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:14,840
to buy new hair clips,
new toys, all the time.

275
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:18,360
Back then, I thought,

276
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,880
"Why does Pakbung spend so much money?"

277
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:24,920
Then Kanah told me you were reselling
those things to your friends at school.

278
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:34,280
And after that,
you stopped buying me anything at all.

279
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,280
I… I saw potential.

280
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,240
I saw your business instincts.
I wanted you to learn about investing,

281
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,480
about turning profit into more profit.

282
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,640
I remember how much fun
you had selling things.

283
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:48,680
You sold everything to everyone.

284
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,520
You even sold stuff
to your homeroom teacher,

285
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,880
until the discipline department
called me in. Remember?

286
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:56,520
The teachers thought
our family was struggling

287
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,720
because I was selling nonstop,

288
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,560
hustling in every possible way.

289
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:09,720
But no matter how good I was at selling,

290
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:11,840
it was never enough to match your greed.

291
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:21,320
I was greedy.

292
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:23,720
I prioritized money over family.

293
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,600
I don't feel like driving today.

294
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:38,920
Oh, okay. Sure, sure.

295
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,560
Come on, come on.

296
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:44,040
I'll drive.

297
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,080
You sit on the back.

298
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,440
Come on.

299
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,160
Hurry. Hop on.

300
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:53,760
Come on.

301
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:00,160
Pakbung, hold onto my waist.

302
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,720
Hold onto my waist.

303
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,040
Alright, you don't want to? Be careful.

304
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:12,880
Hold me like that. Let's go.

305
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,240
Lee, leave the documents on the table.

306
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:40,880
Rachen?

307
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,320
So this is what you love so much?

308
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:50,040
The school you ditched Be Rich for?

309
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,600
Here to visit or to look down on me?

310
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:56,200
I came to see it with my own eyes.

311
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:59,360
You could've told me.
I'd have rolled out the red carpet.

312
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:05,920
What are you really planning?

313
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,240
A plan?

314
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,160
Short-term lesson plans,

315
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:18,480
long-term curriculum plans,

316
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,440
and active learning plans.

317
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:21,920
Trai. I'm not playing.

318
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,720
This is my mom's school, Bro.

319
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,120
And it's my dream too.

320
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,640
So no, I'm not playing.

321
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,560
All your friends have kids now, right?

322
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,320
Ask one or two for me.

323
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:43,640
Trai.

324
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:47,760
Can you talk properly for once
without messing with my head?

325
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:52,920
You're exactly like Dad right now,
stone faced, can't smile.

326
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:57,120
Honestly, now that you're the CEO
of Be Rich like you always wanted,

327
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,320
aren't you happy at all?

328
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:01,480
- This is my happy face.
- Yeah, Botox-level stiff.

329
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,160
Trai.

330
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:12,280
Damn it.

331
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:14,560
What is it? What happened?

332
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:23,480
My phone… I forgot my phone.
I think I left it at the school.

333
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:25,840
I'll be right back.

334
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:28,280
Wait, wait. Hey.

335
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:31,800
Don't go. Why go back for it?
Just leave it there.

336
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:35,000
I'll go get it, just a second.
Wait here. Stay here.

337
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,240
See now? Someone's trying to kill me.

338
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,720
Hello, I need to report an emergency.

339
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:54,520
Desk, the desk.

340
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,040
Come on. One, two, three.

341
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:02,000
This time, the target isn't just me.

342
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:05,200
Last time, it was at this school too,
but it wasn't like this.

343
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,400
I just had someone look into the shares.

344
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,160
Go.

345
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:18,400
- Now, Mrs. Mookmanee probably knows.
- She has to kill people over this?

346
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:20,200
I'll ask her if we survive.

347
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,120
Follow me.

348
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:43,680
Trai.

349
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,920
Rachen. Hey.

350
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:19,720
Rachen!

351
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:27,920
Uh…

352
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:38,440
This doesn't look good. Fall back. Go.

353
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:46,920
Rachen. Rachen.

354
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:53,840
‪Hey!

355
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:03,960
Mr. Trai!

356
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,840
Mr. Trai!

357
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:21,440
Hey. Mr. Rachen! What happened?

358
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:23,280
He got shot.

359
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:25,080
And Trai got shot too.

360
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,240
Are you alright?

361
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,440
I saw the attacker run that way.

362
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:33,560
Call an ambulance.

363
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:37,440
Pakbung, check on Trai.

364
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,160
I'm fine.

365
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,440
- Mr. Rachen!
- Rachen!

366
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:46,840
Mr. Rachen!

367
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:47,760
- Rachen.
- Mr. Rachen.

368
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:49,960
- Rachen.
- Hey.

369
00:30:50,040 --> 00:30:51,000
- Hey.
- Mr. Rachen.

370
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:53,000
- Rachen. Hey.
- Mr. Rachen.

371
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:05,760
So besides me, there's someone else?
Did you see his face?

372
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:07,760
The police arrived really fast.

373
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,000
Everyone had to run.

374
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:14,040
But our people are after that gunman.

375
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:17,880
If we get any leads,
I'll report back right away.

376
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:23,360
I really want to know who he is.

377
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:32,880
Where's Mr. Rachen? What happened to him?

378
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:35,560
Rut, how did you know he's here?

379
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:39,360
I couldn't contact Mr. Rachen all night,
so I tracked his phone signal.

380
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,680
He usually has me check on him.

381
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:44,880
Sometimes, he drinks a lot,
and I have to go pick him up.

382
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:46,280
He's inside, right?

383
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:47,480
Hey.

384
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:48,720
You can't go in yet.

385
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:51,760
Why? Or did Mr. Trai
do something to Mr. Rachen?

386
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,200
He didn't do anything.
The doctor said no visitors.

387
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,240
No visitors at all?

388
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,760
Is it that serious?

389
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,440
Rut.

390
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,000
Calm down. You need to get a grip.

391
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:09,600
Go home for now.

392
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:15,560
If his condition improves,
we'll tell you right away.

393
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:26,840
I didn't want to hurt you, Mr. Rachen.

394
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:38,080
But you got in the way.
Blame your brother.

395
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,360
The doctor said you'll be okay.

396
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,680
Why aren't you waking up?

397
00:32:58,120 --> 00:33:00,040
Dad, don't take him.

398
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:06,120
I know you like Rachen more…

399
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,720
but you already have Mom.

400
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:13,080
Leave me my brother, please.

401
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:15,760
You too.

402
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,920
Don't leave me.

403
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:22,440
Don't go be with Dad.

404
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:25,520
You have to wake up.

405
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,800
I still want to fight with you.

406
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:32,280
I haven't even thanked you

407
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:34,600
for saving me.

408
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:40,840
I know we're not the closest brothers.

409
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:42,440
But I promise,

410
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:45,520
if you wake up this time,

411
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:49,440
I won't mess with you anymore.

412
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:54,160
I'll be a good brother.
I won't take anything from you again.

413
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:07,000
You promise?

414
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:09,960
I promise.

415
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:18,360
Hey, you're awake!

416
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:22,800
Yeah, how could I not wake up
with you being this loud?

417
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,000
Uh, wait.

418
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,280
- Were you pretending to sleep?
- No.

419
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:37,360
Do you remember me?
Do you remember you got shot?

420
00:34:40,440 --> 00:34:43,280
- And you?
- I'm okay.

421
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,320
This isn't like you.

422
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,719
The bullet was lodged in you.

423
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,639
They finished the surgery yesterday.

424
00:34:49,719 --> 00:34:51,520
But you were asleep for a whole day.

425
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,239
Such a wimp, Bro.

426
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:55,960
That's not what you said earlier.

427
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,240
What did I say?

428
00:34:57,960 --> 00:35:01,400
Earlier you said you were scared
I'd leave you to go be with Dad.

429
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:04,400
And you were crying too, right?

430
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:08,560
Hey. That's snot, okay?

431
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:12,560
I never thought you'd
worry about me this much.

432
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:18,400
Doctor. Nurse. The patient's awake.

433
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:21,200
And he won't stop talking nonsense.

434
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,320
It must be snowing today.

435
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:32,280
Mr. Trai's really worried about you.
He hired not only Samlee and me

436
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:35,520
to stay with you, but he also has
Mr. Prarop staying with us.

437
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,880
The attacker's still out there.

438
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,600
We don't even know who it is.

439
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:43,880
Mr. Trai just doesn't want me

440
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:46,080
going anywhere alone.

441
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,720
Why do you sound like
you're bragging about a husband?

442
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:50,960
I mean, a boyfriend?

443
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:56,760
What? I'm not bragging.
I haven't even said anything,

444
00:35:57,360 --> 00:36:01,680
like how Trai can barely eat or sleep
because he wants to look after me,

445
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:05,720
but the doctor
won't let him leave the hospital.

446
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:07,600
Sure.

447
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,080
So annoying.

448
00:36:10,360 --> 00:36:11,720
So cringe.

449
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:17,000
Come on. At least we're together.

450
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:19,920
It's safer.

451
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:21,400
With this full-on protection,

452
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:23,520
who's gonna do anything?

453
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:24,520
Yeah.

454
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,560
Let's go.

455
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,480
Someone's following us. Don't turn around.

456
00:36:30,240 --> 00:36:31,600
Stay still. Look forward.

457
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:39,280
Walk straight ahead. Keep it calm.

458
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,800
Act normal.

459
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,720
Walk normally.

460
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,760
Hurry.

461
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:02,720
Hey.

462
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,640
Why are you following me?

463
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:18,120
Did Mrs. Mookmanee order you to?

464
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:22,440
No, I came on my own. I was worried.

465
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,160
Worried?

466
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:31,480
Last night, you came to me

467
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,800
and tried to drag me outside.

468
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:37,280
You knew what was going
to happen at the school, didn't you?

469
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:40,280
Pakbung, can you stop being so smart?

470
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:43,240
Pretend to be dumb sometimes.
I don't even know how to answer that.

471
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:44,560
So it's true.

472
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:47,520
It was Mrs. Mookmanee's doing, right?

473
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:51,360
I can't say much, Pakbung,

474
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:53,000
because I'm taking a risk too.

475
00:37:53,600 --> 00:37:54,920
But…

476
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:58,480
I'm relieved to see that you're safe.

477
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:01,800
That's all I came to see. I'm going, okay?

478
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:08,000
Mr. Trai wondered
why the police arrived so fast.

479
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,240
You called them, right?

480
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:17,760
I'll go get it, just a second.
Wait here. Stay here.

481
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:26,560
What do I do? But…

482
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:30,800
It'll be fine, right?

483
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:35,640
Mrs. Mook's going after Mr. Rachen.
Mr. Trai's not involved.

484
00:38:44,200 --> 00:38:46,920
Hello. This is the police station, right?

485
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,960
I told you I'm going to protect you.

486
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,320
I don't want you
to be disappointed in me again.

487
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:04,000
I'm sure what happened last night
was Mrs. Mookmanee's doing.

488
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:05,720
Otherwise, my dad wouldn't have known.

489
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,320
She's calling him "Dad" now.

490
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,240
The police believe
there were two groups, sir,

491
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:18,200
based on the way they operated

492
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,760
and the shell casings found.

493
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:27,440
But those who stormed inside used
handguns, live rounds. They meant to kill.

494
00:39:27,520 --> 00:39:31,200
I don't know if Mrs. Mookmanee
meant to scare us or actually kill us…

495
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:36,000
But the one who shot us is the same guy
who's been coming after us all along.

496
00:39:36,080 --> 00:39:38,120
I remember the scar on his wrist.

497
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:47,200
Did you recognize anything?

498
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:52,560
I'm tired. I want to rest.

499
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:54,800
Go wait in my room, everyone.

500
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:56,400
You go too.

501
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:58,760
Yeah, I will.
I'm just waiting until you fall asleep.

502
00:39:58,840 --> 00:40:00,800
No need. Why are you guarding me?

503
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,080
You'll be lonely.

504
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:06,920
- I'm not lonely. Get out.
- No. I'm staying.

505
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,840
Then let Pakbung stay instead.

506
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:22,360
Fine.

507
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:26,920
Pakbung, please take care
of Rachen for me, okay?

508
00:40:37,720 --> 00:40:38,920
I'll help.

509
00:40:44,560 --> 00:40:47,560
Can you eat by yourself,
or do you need me to feed you?

510
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:51,440
You've changed a lot, Pakbung.
Do you realize that?

511
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:53,360
I'm prettier, right?

512
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:58,920
Normally, when you take care of me,

513
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:02,720
when you feed me, you charge money.

514
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:08,840
Since when
do you listen to Trai this much?

515
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:11,680
I…

516
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:14,160
You two are not
just friends anymore, are you?

517
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:23,360
Rachen just got shot.

518
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,080
He needs someone to look after him.

519
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:28,400
But the person looking after him
shouldn't be your girlfriend.

520
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:33,680
Rachen feels safe with Pakbung.

521
00:41:34,600 --> 00:41:36,440
And I trust my girlfriend.

522
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:38,880
But I think

523
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:40,960
Pakbung might not feel
comfortable with it.

524
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,120
She's not the type to overthink.

525
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:50,960
But once there's a girlfriend label,

526
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,800
every little thing
can turn into something.

527
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:06,200
I told you I'm not thinking anything.

528
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:09,560
Maybe think a little?
You're Mr. Trai's girlfriend.

529
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:11,360
How could he tell you
to care for another man?

530
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:17,680
Yeah, that's true.
And he didn't even pay me.

531
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:20,680
That's not the point.

532
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:24,480
Right now, it's like Mr. Trai cares
about Mr. Rachen so much

533
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:28,400
that if Mr. Rachen asked,
he would be ready to hand you over.

534
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:30,760
Hand me over?

535
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,800
For free?

536
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:34,440
Shouldn't he charge money?

537
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:35,720
Pakbung!

538
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:36,960
Be serious!

539
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:41,560
His brother's not well.

540
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:44,880
He just wants someone he can trust
to take care of him.

541
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:50,600
If I got sick, would you let Mr. Trai
take care of me, just the two of us?

542
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:55,000
See?

543
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:58,560
Even if you would have said yes,
you still paused. You hesitated.

544
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,480
But Mr. Trai didn't hesitate at all.

545
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:02,480
He agreed instantly.

546
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,560
If Mr. Trai decides to step aside
for Mr. Rachen, what are you gonna do?

547
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:26,000
Why are you here?

548
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,000
I knew you weren't sleeping.

549
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:34,200
What are you doing?

550
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:37,520
I'm scared of ghosts,
so I want to sleep with you.

551
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:42,400
Nothing is scarier than you, Trai.

552
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:45,400
Go back to your room. I'm resting.

553
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:48,320
I'm resting too. Stop whining.

554
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:54,440
Aren't you curious

555
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:57,520
what I talked about
with Pakbung this afternoon?

556
00:44:01,560 --> 00:44:03,240
Why did you save my life?

557
00:44:15,840 --> 00:44:19,200
You took the bullet for me.
Weren't you scared to die?

558
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,080
I didn't want to help you.

559
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:24,520
- Then why did you?
- Because I had to.

560
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:37,200
So, that means you actually love me.

561
00:44:39,920 --> 00:44:41,120
What?

562
00:44:43,320 --> 00:44:44,960
You protected me with your life.

563
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:48,640
You love me. Admit it.

564
00:44:50,720 --> 00:44:54,800
What the hell are you saying? Gross.
Get out. I'm resting.

565
00:44:57,760 --> 00:45:01,280
If Dad saw that,
he'd be damn proud of you.

566
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:06,520
Proud that I'm a loyal lapdog
who even protects the boss's son?

567
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:11,240
That he was right to love you.

568
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:19,680
I'm his kid, forced by circumstance.
He couldn't choose me.

569
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:22,920
But he chose you to be another son of his.

570
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:25,160
So he had to love you, right?

571
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,200
Why else would he bring you
into his family?

572
00:45:33,920 --> 00:45:36,840
- Come on, let's hug, Big Bro.
- Hey, what are you doing?

573
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:38,160
- Let's hug.
- Get out, Trai.

574
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:39,520
- Let's hug.
- What is this? Gross.

575
00:45:39,600 --> 00:45:41,600
- Come on, Bro.
- Get out. No.

576
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:42,760
Come on. Bros can hug.

577
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:43,800
- You're acting like a kid.
- Are you shy?

578
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:46,080
- Huh?
- Enough. It hurts.

579
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:48,640
Mr. Trai.

580
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,520
Pakbung is calling.

581
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:04,200
Mr. Trai already fell asleep?

582
00:46:05,200 --> 00:46:07,560
No, Mr. Lee. It's nothing.

583
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:10,360
Yes.

584
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:23,680
If Mr. Trai

585
00:46:23,760 --> 00:46:25,880
really steps aside for Mr. Rachen,

586
00:46:26,640 --> 00:46:27,800
what do I do?

587
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:33,600
I don't know anymore.

588
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:35,800
Whatever!

589
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:39,080
Rachen got shot?
Why didn't anyone tell me?

590
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:41,440
I'm telling you right now, aren't I?

591
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:44,560
Today, you're going to visit
Rachen at the hospital.

592
00:46:45,480 --> 00:46:48,280
Hospital? I don't like hospitals.

593
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:53,240
Mom, hospitals are full of sick people.

594
00:46:53,320 --> 00:46:54,840
They're depressing.

595
00:46:55,560 --> 00:46:58,240
Uh… then, should I go instead, ma'am?

596
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:02,840
If you want an update on Mr. Rachen,
I can go check for you.

597
00:47:04,040 --> 00:47:05,320
You go there often enough already.

598
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:12,280
Uh, I… I go
because Ms. Mika ordered me to.

599
00:47:12,800 --> 00:47:15,000
Ms. Mika didn't want Pakbung

600
00:47:15,080 --> 00:47:16,920
getting too close to Mr. Rachen,

601
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:19,720
so I had to keep an eye on them.

602
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:21,800
But that night,

603
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:24,880
Mika didn't order you to call the police.

604
00:47:33,880 --> 00:47:36,320
You always like to go beyond your orders,
don't you, Yongyut?

605
00:47:44,040 --> 00:47:45,120
Mrs. Mookmanee.

606
00:47:50,520 --> 00:47:53,240
Our people tailed him all the way
to the outskirts, ma'am.

607
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:56,880
And then, he just vanished.

608
00:47:59,160 --> 00:48:01,720
This is the clearest shot

609
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:03,320
the CCTV captured.

610
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,400
You can't even find a single man.

611
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:09,120
Then I have no reason
to keep any of you around.

612
00:48:10,640 --> 00:48:12,520
Right now, I've got our men

613
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:14,640
spreading out
and searching that area, ma'am.

614
00:48:15,240 --> 00:48:16,200
Good.

615
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:19,160
Because I'd really like to know

616
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:22,680
whether that man or your corpse

617
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:24,760
will be easier to find.

618
00:48:25,880 --> 00:48:29,040
Mrs. Mook, I'll find him.

619
00:48:50,840 --> 00:48:54,640
That's Mrs. Mookmanee for you. Way faster
at tracking things down than Trai.

620
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:10,320
I'm not going to get caught.

621
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:12,840
Not until I see the end of you all.

622
00:49:16,040 --> 00:49:17,720
BE RICH CLOSES 2023
WITH 10 BILLION BAHT NET PROFIT

623
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:27,920
I'm fine.

624
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:31,080
Honestly, I think
I should go back to my condo.

625
00:49:35,040 --> 00:49:38,000
I had the maid
clean your room for you, Mr. Rachen.

626
00:49:38,080 --> 00:49:41,720
I hope you don't mind
that I didn't visit you at the hospital.

627
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:45,440
No one told me, after all.

628
00:49:51,080 --> 00:49:52,000
Rachen.

629
00:49:54,200 --> 00:49:57,080
I think you and I should sleep
in Dad's room together.

630
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:00,440
It'll be easier for me
to take care of you.

631
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:02,720
It's fine.

632
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:05,080
I've got someone to take care of me.

633
00:50:05,160 --> 00:50:07,080
Here I am. I'm here.

634
00:50:09,320 --> 00:50:10,760
Sorry I'm late.

635
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:14,160
I was packing my stuff.

636
00:50:14,760 --> 00:50:15,720
Pakbung?

637
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:20,360
I hired Pakbung to take care of me,
full-time.

638
00:50:21,840 --> 00:50:24,440
Mr. Rachen just called me this morning,

639
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:26,560
so I didn't get to tell you.

640
00:50:28,920 --> 00:50:30,840
Where should I put this bag?

641
00:50:31,840 --> 00:50:33,920
Just leave it in my dad's room.

642
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:35,840
You'll be staying with me anyway,

643
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:37,520
24/7.

644
00:50:42,880 --> 00:50:44,160
You don't mind, do you?

645
00:50:51,200 --> 00:50:54,520
That's good. Then you won't have
to go back and forth.

646
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:21,960
You're really going to have me
sleep in the same room as you?

647
00:51:22,840 --> 00:51:24,520
Trai still hasn't said anything at all.

648
00:51:25,440 --> 00:51:28,360
But I don't feel okay with it.

649
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:31,480
Then if you're uncomfortable,
why didn't you say so earlier?

650
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:35,440
Or were you trying to test Trai?

651
00:51:39,920 --> 00:51:42,400
You wanted to test
your brother too, didn't you?

652
00:51:43,160 --> 00:51:45,840
Trai told me he won't take
anything from me anymore.

653
00:51:47,880 --> 00:51:49,600
That probably includes you.

654
00:52:22,360 --> 00:52:23,280
How is Rachen?

655
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:31,520
Good.

656
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:33,360
Not stubborn, not naughty,

657
00:52:33,440 --> 00:52:36,440
easy to handle, easy to understand.

658
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:39,880
The kitchen is this way, right?

659
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:50,360
Pakbung.

660
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:52,800
And tonight, you…

661
00:52:54,240 --> 00:52:55,800
Do you have minced pork?

662
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:03,240
We have a cook. What do you want to eat?

663
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:09,720
Mr. Rachen wants basil minced pork,

664
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:12,480
spicy, with a runny yolk fried egg.

665
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:18,360
I'll have the cook make it.

666
00:53:20,960 --> 00:53:23,160
Mr. Rachen wants my cooking.

667
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:25,360
I'm making it for him.

668
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:34,600
Then make some for me too.

669
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:36,360
No.

670
00:53:36,440 --> 00:53:37,640
Why?

671
00:53:40,520 --> 00:53:42,880
Didn't you want me
to take care of Mr. Rachen?

672
00:53:43,640 --> 00:53:46,480
Yeah, but…

673
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:48,920
I'll take good care of Mr. Rachen,

674
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:50,400
not because you asked,

675
00:53:50,480 --> 00:53:52,560
but because Mr. Rachen hired me.

676
00:53:52,640 --> 00:53:54,200
He's paying me extra.

677
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:57,200
So I have to treat him extra special.

678
00:53:58,120 --> 00:53:59,440
More special than anyone else.

679
00:54:04,040 --> 00:54:06,880
But I'm not anyone else. I'm…

680
00:54:06,960 --> 00:54:08,440
Pakbung.

681
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:10,320
Mr. Rachen is calling for you.

682
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:14,520
What did you say?

683
00:54:15,160 --> 00:54:16,280
You're…

684
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:18,760
You're what?

685
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:32,240
Go check on Rachen.

686
00:54:44,960 --> 00:54:46,320
Pakbung. Pakbung.

687
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:48,520
Pakbung.

688
00:54:53,880 --> 00:54:54,840
Well, I…

689
00:54:57,400 --> 00:54:58,680
Mr. Trai.

690
00:54:59,680 --> 00:55:02,680
Lee's calling.
The police want to question you again.

691
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:17,520
Yes?

692
00:55:21,480 --> 00:55:23,800
<i>Trai told me he won't take</i>
<i>anything from me anymore.</i>

693
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:26,040
That probably includes you.

694
00:55:26,120 --> 00:55:29,720
That if Mr. Rachen asked,
he would be ready to hand you over.

695
00:55:30,800 --> 00:55:31,640
Fine.

696
00:55:31,720 --> 00:55:33,200
Try handing me over.

697
00:55:33,280 --> 00:55:35,600
I'll blacklist you out of my life forever.

698
00:55:40,480 --> 00:55:42,000
So you and Trai are dating now?

699
00:55:49,200 --> 00:55:50,320
Did Mr. Trai tell you?

700
00:55:53,440 --> 00:55:56,360
No. He wouldn't.

701
00:55:56,440 --> 00:55:58,360
I just guessed from how you're acting.

702
00:55:59,680 --> 00:56:01,440
You're really into him, aren't you?

703
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:04,840
So, are you going
to congratulate me or not?

704
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:08,360
If not, keep it to yourself.

705
00:56:10,640 --> 00:56:12,360
I used to admire you, you know.

706
00:56:12,440 --> 00:56:15,880
You weren't obsessed with love,
didn't look like anyone's slave.

707
00:56:17,200 --> 00:56:21,040
But now, you're starting
to look more and more like me.

708
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,640
You've seen it too, haven't you?

709
00:56:23,720 --> 00:56:25,120
You're not

710
00:56:25,200 --> 00:56:27,280
Trai's first priority.

711
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:29,560
Even now that you're dating,

712
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:33,240
there are still other things
he cares about more than you.

713
00:56:36,600 --> 00:56:39,280
Be careful, Pakbung. Be careful.

714
00:56:40,680 --> 00:56:44,680
One day, you'll get hurt, like I did.

715
00:56:47,640 --> 00:56:48,800
Are you done?

716
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:51,080
Thanks for the review.

717
00:56:51,160 --> 00:56:55,000
But I'll date him myself.
I'll decide for myself.

718
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:57,040
Even if it doesn't work out,

719
00:56:57,120 --> 00:57:00,040
I'm not giving him back to anyone.

720
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:03,520
Don't get your hopes up.

721
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,640
Then just wait for the day you regret it.

722
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:14,480
Okay. And if you want to gloat,

723
00:57:15,120 --> 00:57:17,120
only come to me on that day.

724
00:57:17,840 --> 00:57:20,680
Don't come so often. It's boring.

725
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:33,480
Such a smart mouth.

726
00:57:36,960 --> 00:57:40,120
And Trai just floats above every problem,
like he doesn't care about anyone.

727
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:45,360
Ms. Mika.

728
00:57:47,520 --> 00:57:48,960
Doesn't this house
teach its maids anything?

729
00:57:49,040 --> 00:57:51,520
Letting a guest walk in
carrying things myself.

730
00:57:53,520 --> 00:57:55,440
Fruit. I brought them for Rachen.

731
00:57:58,760 --> 00:57:59,880
Peel them for him too.

732
00:58:03,040 --> 00:58:04,000
Where is Rachen?

733
00:58:08,360 --> 00:58:10,920
He's upstairs. I'll take you there.

734
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:17,680
- Hey.
- Mika. Mika.

735
00:58:17,760 --> 00:58:18,600
Hey. Pakbung.

736
00:58:18,680 --> 00:58:20,040
- Stop!
- Pakbung, stop.

737
00:58:20,120 --> 00:58:22,120
- Stop.
- You can't take care of Pakbung,

738
00:58:22,200 --> 00:58:23,800
the same way
you couldn't take care of Dad.

739
00:58:23,880 --> 00:58:26,000
You can't take care
of anyone at all, Trai.

740
00:58:26,080 --> 00:58:28,440
I think we should reconsider our status.

741
00:58:29,640 --> 00:58:30,680
Pakbung.

742
00:58:33,840 --> 00:58:35,240
- Pakbung.
- Pakbung.

743
00:58:35,920 --> 00:58:37,160
<i>You're out of chances now, Trai.</i>

744
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:40,360
A capable man like you…

745
00:58:41,600 --> 00:58:43,440
With a sponsor, you could go even further.

746
00:58:45,800 --> 00:58:47,360
We're together almost every day,

747
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:49,600
but I still don't know anything about you.

748
00:58:55,120 --> 00:58:55,920
Hey!

749
00:58:56,000 --> 00:58:57,720
You're really nosy, huh?

750
00:59:04,880 --> 00:59:05,920
You bastard!

751
00:59:53,920 --> 00:59:55,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
